1. Make artificial diamonds out of graphite.

4. Nobody drinks the unpleasant water, but it's too expensive to just throw away. Carbon sequestered!

snippet.textDisplay: LMFAO i'm so sorry in advance and I get it I would have done this the exact same way  but so many of these parts were over complicated. Again i'm sorry. For the soda stream they sell gas cylinders that are used to carbonate the water. Once those are empty you can either exchange them or buy new already filled cylinders. Instead of building your own gas cylinder you could have gone on eBay and bought a used empty soda stream cylinder. Twisted of the the cylinder head and filled it wit co2/Dry Ice while weighing it to make sure you don't over fill it.  The whole "make my own gas tank" was completely unnecessary. Also you could have used ceramic fiber "blanket" to create some sort of holding device to hold the diamonds while you hit it with the torch, because its a fiber blanket you could have had a nice oxygen flow rising up under the diamonds by placing the oxygen nozzle beneath the blanket end letting the gas rise up and react with the diamonds.
